metadata.name: Tobacco Leaf
metadata.description:
A life devoted to tobacco. Tobacco is a very laborious  job. Tobacco cracking is done at night and in summer because tobacco softens on hot summer days.
Uncle who collects tobacco lost two of his fingers at a very young age, and the effort he put in can be seen from his hands.

Artist: Volkan KARAGÜLLEOĞLU 

Edition: 1/1
Camera: Nikon D600
Camera Settings: f/4.2 1/1600 sn iso-100
